# Python Webserver

A minimal HTTP server written in **pure Python** — no frameworks, no dependencies. Useful for serving static HTML pages locally.

## Usage

```bash
git clone https://github.com/albertguedes/simple-python-webserver.git
python src/http_server.py
```

Access at `http://localhost:8000`

## Testing

```bash
python -m unittest tests/test_http_server.py
```

## Tech Stack

- Python standard library (`http.server`)
- `unittest` (stdlib)

